**Damage Report:**

**Vehicle Make/Model:** [Insert Vehicle Information]
**Date of Inspection:** [Insert Date]

**Location of Damage:**
- The front fender of the vehicle shows significant damage. There appears to be a large dent or indentation on the lower portion of the fender near the wheel well.

**Type of Damage:**
- The damage appears to be a dent or impact damage. The surface of the fender has been deformed, and the paint has been disturbed around the affected area. There are visible scratches and dents that suggest the fender has been hit by an object, possibly another vehicle or a heavy object.

**Additional Observations:**
- The tire and wheel well appear to be in good condition with no visible signs of damage.
- The surrounding area of the fender shows some minor scuff marks, which may have occurred during the incident causing the main dent.

**Conclusion:**
The vehicle has sustained damage to the front fender. The extent of the damage requires further assessment to determine the appropriate course of action, such as repair or replacement. It is recommended to schedule an appointment with a collision repair shop to evaluate the damage fully and provide an estimate for repairs.

**Prepared By:**
[Your Name]  
Insurance Adjuster  
[Your Company]  
[Contact Information]  

**Attachments:**

**End of Report.**
